  "texts": [
    "Our results reveal that while larger and newer models generally outperform their smaller and older counterparts in accuracy, most models exhibit poor performance in recognizing unanswerable questions and managing uncertainty.",
    "Notably, only three models, with GPT-4o standing out, effectively vary their confidence levels.",
    "We find that LLMs' tendency towards overconfidence and inability to recognize knowledge gaps pose potential risks in clinical applications.",
    "These findings underscore the need for developing more sophisticated mechanisms within LLMs to handle uncertainty and ambiguity, as well as the importance of evolving benchmarks and evaluation metrics that capture the complexities of clinical reasoning.",
    "To evaluate the metacognitive abilities of Large LLMs in medical contexts, we based our assessment on MedQA-USMLE, a subset of MedQA, due to the other benchmarks included in MultiMedQA lacking both quality and clinical relevance."
  ],
